Foyston Gordon & Payne Inc Buys 23,335 Shares of Novo Nordisk A/S (NVO)


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 8th, 2017 // No Comments




Foyston Gordon & Payne Inc boosted its stake in  Novo Nordisk A/S (NYSE:NVO) by 24.8% during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor  owned 117,392 shares of the company’s stock after buying an additional 23,335 shares during the period. Foyston Gordon & Payne Inc’s holdings in Novo Nordisk A/S were worth $4,024,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
A number of other hedge funds have also recently bought and sold shares of NVO. Commerzbank Aktiengesellschaft FI raised its position in shares of  Novo Nordisk A/S by 103.1% in the fourth quarter. Commerzbank Aktiengesellschaft FI now owns 117,109 shares of the company’s stock valued at $4,200,000 after buying an additional 59,438 shares during the last quarter.  FNY Partners Fund LP acquired a new position in  Novo Nordisk A/S during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $359,000.  Wetherby Asset Management Inc. increased its position in  Novo Nordisk A/S by 5.5% in the fourth quarter. Wetherby Asset Management Inc. now owns 25,832 shares of the company’s stock valued at $926,000 after buying an additional 1,352 shares during the period.  Comerica Bank increased its position in  Novo Nordisk A/S by 8.6% in the fourth quarter. Comerica Bank now owns 193,281 shares of the company’s stock valued at $6,906,000 after buying an additional 15,264 shares during the period.  Finally, Cutter & CO Brokerage Inc. acquired a new position in  Novo Nordisk A/S during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $6,403,000. 6.34% of the stock is currently owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Novo Nordisk A/S alerts:



Novo Nordisk A/S (NVO) opened at 42.01 on Friday. The company has a market cap of $104.85 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 18.31 and a beta of 0.63. The company has a 50-day moving average of $42.51 and a 200-day moving average of $37.36. Novo Nordisk A/S has a one year low of $30.89 and a one year high of $57.41. 
